<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1398,313,516]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque-Schmaltz" authorityYear="1815" box="[189,339,313,339]" class="Clitellata" family="Lumbricidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lumbricinae">Lumbricinae</taxonomicName>
of large to very large size, post-clitellar trapezoidal section. Pigmentation brown to dark brown. Prostomium epilobous, closed. Longitudinal furrows in the peristomium. Nephridial pores “en solfège” (irregularly distributed). Spermathecal pores at least in two intersegments, between 9/10 and 13/14, or 13/14 and 15/16, sometimes multiple. Anterior septa strongly thickened. Male pores in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1331,1354,419,445]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">½</emphasis>
15, usually with porophores. Gizzard in 17–20 (21, 22). Typhlosole pinnate. Two or four pairs of seminal vesicles in (9, 10) 11, 12.
</paragraph>
